"12oz. can served in a shaker pint.  Pours a dull orange hue a slightly hazy clarity and a loose, pink-tinged, one inch white head that quickly sizzles and pops as it dissipates into a fizzy band around the shoulders.  Blood oranges are very apparent in the nose - it's almost reminiscent of Fanta orange cola.  Saltiness is evident from the first quaff and the blood orange is a bit diminished in the flavor profile; coming off spritzy and citrusy.  Mouthfeel is light and lively with a kiss of acidity that lightly stimulates the salivary glands along the sides of the cheeks.  I've only had this style a couple of times and they all have left a slightly different impression.  That said, I found this enjoyable and look forward to visiting it again during warmer weather."
