"Why not?  This stuff pours a clear straw-brass topped by a finger of off-white foam.  The nose comprises orange zest, lemon peel, very light biscuit, and a kiss on each cheek, one from Ginger and one from Lime.  We're popular.  The taste centers on tart blood orange and lemon zest, but also in the mix are mild ginger and a vague sweetness (one that underflows everything), along with a twinge of brine in the aftertaste.  The body straddles the line between hefty light and light medium (leaning toward the former, though), with a light moderate carbonation and a wet feel.  Overall, a very enjoyable gose that doesn't overdo the tartness, maintaining a high degree of drinkability.  I'm not sure if I prefer this one over the regular gose, but I can say that I wouldn't turn down either were they offered to me.  Good times."
