"perhaps i am alone in this, but i prefer the straight up gose they do to this one by a considerable margin. its just not adding all that much, aside from sweetness, that i really think doesnt belong in this style based on refreshment. it adds a nice color to the brew, and stains the head a little bit in the glass. the fruit adds a nice citrus tang to the nose, which i would describe as the fruits greatest contribution to the beer. its zesty and a cool wrinkle with the coriander that is pretty heavy in here too. the flavor though, the fruit never comes through as much as it does in the nose, and it just seems sort of sweet to me, covers up the salt, and presents itself more as a fruit beer than as a gose. i liked the simplicity of the other one, but i can see the appeal here too. its still refreshing, but not as dry as i would have hoped. still acidic and still brilliantly carbonated. cool project."
