"12 ounce can, no canning date that I could find.  Served in a pint glass, the beer pours a mostly clear golden/orange color with about an inch off-white head.  Head retention is decent, and there isn't much lacing at all.  The brew smells like orange soda, lime/citrus, and a bit of saltiness.  I like the taste of this, it tastes like blood oranges, salt, limes, and some Tang citrus drink.  It's sweet, tart, and a bit salty.  Mouthfeel/body is light/medium, it's a bit coating and is very refreshing.  Even on a cold day, I'm still liking this.  It's a good sessionable brew, just the thing I'm looking for when I want to end the night with one more good beer that isn't very high in ABV.  And I figure this would be really good on a hot day.  I'm liking this one more and more the longer I drink it!  Definitely worth trying, and it's priced well at $8.99 a 6 pack.  Yeah, I think I'll be buying this again soon."
