"Poured out of a 12 oz can into my stange glass, this beer pours a slightly cloudy/hazy but mainly clear light to medium golden color with a slight orange hue and lots of little bubbles rapidly and continuously rising to the top of the glass.  Has nice, big, fluffy looking white head that is well over an inch thick when first poured into the glass that settles, pretty quickly at that unfortunately, to a thin white ring lining the inside of the glass with practically zero lacing.  Has a very distinct orange/citrus aroma along with what I do believe is a hint of wheat.  Has a nice slightly sour and tart, yet also sweet at the same time somehow, citrus/orange flavor upfront along with a sort of musty, earthy bread like quality and of course a nice hint of salt.  Has  a very crisp, yet smooth, slightly prickly, medium to full bodied mouthfeel with moderate carbonation.  A really fine effort here.  Quite and enjoyable beer.  Very easy to drink in the way good beer should be.  Everyone should try this beer!"
