"Poured from a can into a snifter, the beer is a amber-tinted orange color, slightly hazed and vibrant, with no evidence of the scant head that was there on the pour. Aromas of toasted grains, salt water/brine, and subtle raspberry and citrus tart notes. Flavors are very tart and sour forward, nicely balanced, with a blast of tart blood orange sweetness, ocean water saltiness, and a solid sour undertone. Orange rind and subtle roast highlights throughout. The body is full, but extremely dry and crisp. The aftertaste is more of the rich blood orange, with the tart raspberry shining through. The finish has a sour linger, although otherwise crisp and dry. Very refreshing, drinkable brew."
